name: Επιγραφικό μουσείο
description: The Epigraphical museum exhibits 13536 inscriptions and is the biggest of its kind in the world. It displays collections of inscriptions from different historic periods of Greece, as well as some Latin and Jewish inscriptions.

name: Μουσείο Αρχαίας Αγοράς Αθηνών
bibliography: Camp II J. McK., The Athenian Agora: Excavations in the Heart of Classical Athens, London 1986 Camp II J. Mck, The Athenian Agora. A guide to the Εxcavation and Μuseum 1990 Camp II J. McK, The Athenian Agora, A Short Guide to the Excavations, Excavation
note: Housed in the restored building of the Stoa of Attalos, the exhibition of the Museum contains findings of the American School of Classical Studies in Ancient Agora dating from Neolithic times until the post-Byzantine period and the Ottoman era.
operator: Α' Εφορεία Προϊστορικών και Κλασικών Αρχαιοτήτων
transport: Metro (200m from Monastiraki station), Electric Railway (350m from Thisseio station), Bus (150m from Monastiraki station)

name: Ιδιωτική Συλλογή Έργων Τέχνης Εθνικής Τραπέζης
name:en: Art Collection of National Bank of Greece
description:en: The Art Collection of National Bank of Greece Museum includes about 1300 artworks made by great painters and sculptors of the 19th and 20th century.

name: Νομισματικό Μουσείο
description: The Numismatic Museum owns 500.000 acquisitions –mostly coins as well as medals, lead bullae, gems, weights, obeloi and talents- dated from the 14th century BC until today

name: Δημοτική Πινακοθήκη Πειραιά
description: Operating from 1957, exposes works of modern Greek painters and after systematic study, documentation and at regular intervals will be posting newer artists, mainly of Piraeus. Also exposed a part of the collection of C. Kastrioti sculptures
note: distinct node for the Gallery as there are different start_date, purpose and other details, which are not shared with the old post office building, on which is now hosted.

name: Επιτροπή Ποντιακών Μελετών
description: Η Επιτροπή Ποντιακών Μελετών είναι σωματείο επιστημονικό, μη κερδοσκοπικού χαρακτήρα, ιδρύθηκε το 1927 στην Αθήνα. Η Βιβλιοθήκη λειτουργεί από το 1990, περιλαμβάνει 5.000 τίτλους περίπου και συνεχώς ανανεώνεται.

name: Ιστορικό Αρχείο Πολιτιστικού Ιδρύματος Ομίλου Πειραιώς

note: Το Μουσείο Ακρόπολης, από τα σπουδαιότερα στον κόσμο, περιλαμβάνει μοναδικά αριστουργήματα, κυρίως πρωτότυπα έργα της αρχαϊκής και κλασικής ελληνικής τέχνης, που συνδέονται άμεσα με τον ιερό βράχο της αθηναϊκής Ακρόπολης.
